description: Retention of a covered seated spectator stand on the eastern edge of the site and main sports pitch; associated hardstanding to accommodate car parking (Retrospective Application).
decision_conditions: The development hereby approved shall be in accordance with drawing/document numbers: Transport Statement-R01, prepared by Vectos, dated November 2019; Travel Plan, prepared by Vectos, dated February 2021; Figure 6 (on-site parking plan); Design and Access Statement-rev-xx, prepard by Stiff+Trevillion, dated July 2019; PL-02-110; PL-02-100; PL-02-101; PL-03-100; PL-04-100; Application Form, prepared by Mr A Trevillion, dated 23.07.2019.

Reason: For the avoidance of doubt, and in the interests of proper planning. | A minimum of seven of the approved car parking spaces shall be appropriately designed and designated for disabled person car parking. An additional five of the approved car parking spaces shall be enlarged bays and appropriately designed for future use as designated disabled person car parking spaces. These spaces shall be available for use within three months of the issuing of this decision notice, at the latest, and shall permanently be retained as such thereafter, unless enlarged bays are to be repurposed as designated disabled person bays.

Reason: To ensure appropriate disabled person and enlarged car parking is provided in accordance with Policy T6 .5 of The London Plan and Ealing's Supplementary Planning Document 'Sustainable Transport for New Development'. | All 115 approved car parking spaces shall be installed with active or passive electric or other Ultra-Low Emission vehicle charging infrastructure facilities. The car charging infrastructure facilities for every approved car parking space shall be installed within six months of the issuing of this decision notice, at the latest, and shall permanently be retained as such thereafter, unless passive vehicle charging points are being upgraded into active vehicle charging points.

Reason: To ensure appropriate electric vehicle charging points are provided to encourage the use of sustainable modes of transport, in accordance with Paragraph 105 of the NPPF, Policy T6 and T6.4 of The London Plan and Ealing's Supplementary Planning Document 'Sustainable Transport for New Development'. | A minimum of 82 onsite cycle parking spaces shall be provided onsite within three months of the issuing of this decision notice, as stated in the submitted Transport Statement and Travel Plan. This minimum level of onsite cycle parking shall permanently be retained as such thereafter.

Reason: To ensure appropriate cycle parking is provided to encourage the use of sustainable modes of transport, in accordance with Policy T5 of The London Plan and Ealing's Supplementary Planning Document 'Sustainable Transport for New Development'. | Within three months of the issuing of this decision notice, a Delivery Servicing and Car Parking Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved details shall be adhered to in perpetuity.

Reason: To minimise impacts on residential amenity and ensure pupil safety in accordance with Policies T6 and T7 of The London Plan and Policy 7A of Ealing's Development Management DPD. | (a) A suitable scheme of proposed tree planting and tree pits shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority within three months of the issuing of this decision notice. The scheme shall include the following comprehensive details:
- Full planting specification - tree size, species, the numbers of trees and any changes from the original application proposals.
- Comprehensive details of ground/tree pit preparation to include:
- Plans detailing adequate soil volume provision to allow the tree to grow to maturity
- Engineering solutions to demonstrate the tree will not interfere with structures (e.g. root 	barriers/deflectors) in the future
- Five-year post planting maintenance and inspection schedule.
(b) The approved trees and pits shall all be planted during the nearest planting season (1st October to 31st March inclusive) following the approval of details.

(c) If the approved trees or any on-site trees within 50 metres of the spectator stand die, are removed, uprooted, significantly damaged, become diseased or malformed within five years from the date of planting, they must be replaced during the nearest planting season (1st October to 31st March inclusive). The replacement tree species shall be agreed in writing with the Council's Tree Services prior to planting and shall be retained as such thereafter.

Reason: To ensure appropriate tree planting is delivered in accordance with Principle 15 of the NPPF, Policy G7 of The London Plan, Policy 5.10 of Ealing's Development Management DPD and Ealing Council's SPG 9 - Trees and Development Guidelines. | Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015, no development, extensions or alterations, nor any provision of new hardstanding, shall be carried out without the prior permission of the Local Planning Authority, obtained through the submission of a planning application.

Reason: To safeguard Metropolitan Open Land and Community Open Space and manage future development proposals in accordance with Paragraph 145 of the NPPF, Policies S5 and G3 of The London Plan, Policy 2.18 of Ealing's Development Plan Document and Policy 5.2 in the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy. | Within three months of the issuing of this decision notice, details of onsite waste storage provision shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved details shall be implemented within three months of the Council's approval of waste storage provision and shall be permanently retained as such thereafter.

Reason: To reduce impacts on residential amenity, particularly on match days, caused by littering, by ensuring appropriate waste storage provision in accordance with Policy SI 7 of The London Plan, Policy 7A of Ealing's Development Management DPD and Ealing Council's SPG 4 - Refuse and Recycling Facilities.
